**`update_issue` and `update_review` accept empty mutations.** When called with all `None` options and empty slices, these methods still read the entry, build an empty `mutations` vec, and call `self.repo.update()` — which creates a new commit on the entity ref with an identical tree. This wastes space and creates noise in the ref history. There should be a guard: if `mutations.is_empty()`, return the current entity without writing.